from cfb charlie brett subject re lead acid battery concrete michael covington mcovingt write thi topic wa beat to death a year or so ago the concrete be not the problem lead-acid battery often fail from disuse not be charge for a long time but there no way the concrete floor could be the cause of the problem ditto the only remote and i do say remote possibility be that if the grind wa real cold the battery might freeze an split but then it would probably freeze anyway charlie brett ft collin co 